<define-tag description>security update</define-tag>
<define-tag moreinfo>
<p>Multiple buffer overflows have been found in the VideoLAN media player.
Processing malformed subtitles or movie files could lead to denial of
service and potentially the execution of arbitrary code.</p>

<p>For the stable distribution (wheezy), these problems have been fixed in
version 2.0.3-5+deb7u1.</p>

<p>For the testing distribution (jessie), these problems have been fixed in
version 2.1.0-1.</p>

<p>For the unstable distribution (sid), these problems have been fixed in
version 2.1.0-1.</p>

<p>We recommend that you upgrade your vlc packages.</p>
</define-tag>

